{"type":"message","id":"49963604","parentId":"22b70ca3","timestamp":"2026-07-07T15:00:50.269Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6476194339c643a1a0f7b26a","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# Why Most AI Agents Drift\n\n**Published:** 2026-07-07 15:00 UTC\n**LinkedIn URL:** https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7480274563235254272/\n**Characters:** 838\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Key Message:** #4 — Benchmark-first AI Agent development\n\n---\n\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝘄𝗼𝗿𝗸𝘀 𝘁𝗼𝗱𝗮𝘆. 𝗜𝘁 𝗯𝗿𝗲𝗮𝗸𝘀 𝘁𝗼𝗺𝗼𝗿𝗿𝗼𝘄. 𝗬𝗼𝘂 𝗱𝗼𝗻'𝘁 𝗸𝗻𝗼𝘄 𝘄𝗵𝘆.\n\nSound familiar?\n\nThis is the drift problem. Most agents have no anchor. They optimize for whatever feels right in the moment — but there's no fixed target.\n\nThe fix: benchmark + reward function.\n\nDefine the outcome. Make it measurable. Let the agent optimize toward it.\n\nEvery successful iteration is progress. Every failure is a signal. No guessing.\n\nTraditional software has tests. AI agents need benchmarks.\n\nWithout one, you're not building a system. You're building a feeling.\n\nWhat's your agent's benchmark — or are you hoping it figures itself out?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #MachineLearning #SoftwareEngineering #TDD\n\n---\n\n## Performance\n\n| Metric | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| Impressions | _pending_ |\n| Engagements | _pending_ |\n| Comments | _pending_ |\n| Shares | _pending_ |\n","path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/2026-07-07-why-most-ai-agents-drift.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"content\": \"# Why Most AI Agents Drift\\n\\n**Published:** 2026-07-07 15:00 UTC\\n**LinkedIn URL:** https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7480274563235254272/\\n**Characters:** 838\\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\\n**Key Message:** #4 — Benchmark-first AI Agent development\\n\\n---\\n\\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝘄𝗼𝗿𝗸𝘀 𝘁𝗼𝗱𝗮𝘆. 𝗜𝘁 𝗯𝗿𝗲𝗮𝗸𝘀 𝘁𝗼𝗺𝗼𝗿𝗿𝗼𝘄. 𝗬𝗼𝘂 𝗱𝗼𝗻'𝘁 𝗸𝗻𝗼𝘄 𝘄𝗵𝘆.\\n\\nSound familiar?\\n\\nThis is the drift problem. Most agents have no anchor. They optimize for whatever feels right in the moment — but there's no fixed target.\\n\\nThe fix: benchmark + reward function.\\n\\nDefine the outcome. Make it measurable. Let the agent optimize toward it.\\n\\nEvery successful iteration is progress. Every failure is a signal. No guessing.\\n\\nTraditional software has tests. AI agents need benchmarks.\\n\\nWithout one, you're not building a system. You're building a feeling.\\n\\nWhat's your agent's benchmark — or are you hoping it figures itself out?\\n\\n#AI #AIAgents #MachineLearning #SoftwareEngineering #TDD\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Performance\\n\\n| Metric | Value |\\n|--------|-------|\\n| Impressions | _pending_ |\\n| Engagements | _pending_ |\\n| Comments | _pending_ |\\n| Shares | _pending_ |\\n\", \"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/2026-07-07-why-most-ai-agents-drift.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783436439257,"responseId":"mBRNaqChJIqM6dgPkLuekAM"}}
